Mobile device IP address
Mobile operating system and browser type
Tracking Technologies and Cookies
We use Cookies and similar tracking technologies to monitor activity and store certain information. These may include:
Cookies or Browser Cookies:
Small files stored on Your Device to enhance functionality. You can refuse Cookies via browser settings, but doing so may limit certain features.
Web Beacons:
Small electronic files (e.g., clear gifs, pixel tags) embedded in certain sections of the Service to analyze usage and ensure system integrity.
Types of Cookies We Use:
Necessary Cookies:
Essential for the operation of the Website.
Functional Cookies:
Remember Your preferences to enhance the user experience.
Acceptance Cookies:
Record Your acceptance of Cookie use.
